obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (11850)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11850&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called ^1`
  line `[the Mahatma Gandhi`
  line `National Rural Employment Guarantee Act], 2005.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different States or for different areas in`
  line `a State and any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a`
  line `reference to the coming into force of that provision in such State or, as the case may be, in such area:`
  line
  line `Provided that this Act shall be applicable to the whole of the territory to which it extends within a`
  line `period of five years from the date of enactment of this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 2009, s. 2, for the National Rural Employment Guarantee Act (w.e.f. 2-10-2009).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 23 of 2007, s. 2, (w.e.f. 6-6-2007).`
  line
  line `3. 2nd February, 2006, vide notification No. S.O. 87(E), dated 24th January, 2006, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II`
  line `sec.3(ii).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (11851)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11851&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "adult" means a person who has completed his eighteenth years of age;`
  line
  line `(b) "applicant" means the head of a household or any of its other adult members who has applied`
  line `for employment under the Scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) "Block" means a community development area within a district comprising a group of Gram`
  line Panchayats;
  line
  line `(d) "Central Council" means the Central Employment Guarantee Council constituted under subsection`
  line `(1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) "District Programme Coordinator" means an officer of the State Government designated as`
  line `such under sub-section (1) of section 14 for implementation of the Scheme in a district;`
  line
  line `(f) "household" means the members of a family related to each other by blood, marriage or`
  line `adoption and normally residing together and sharing meals or holding a common ration card;`
  line
  line `(g)" implementing agency" includes any department of the Central Government or a State`
  line `Government, a Zila Parishad, Panchayat at intermediate level, Gram Panchayat or any local authority`
  line `or Government undertaking or non-governmental organisation authorised by the Central Government`
  line `or the State Government to undertake the implementation of any work taken up under a Scheme;`
  line
  line `(h) "minimum wage", in relation to any area, means the minimum wage fixed by the State`
  line `Government under section 3 of the Minimum Wages Act, 1948 (11 of 1948) for agricultural labourers`
  line `as applicable in that area;`
  line
  line `(i) "National Fund" means the National Employment Guarantee Fund established under subsection`
  line `(1) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(j) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(k) "preferred work" means any work which is taken up for implementation on a priority basis`
  line `under a Scheme;`
  line
  line `(l) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "Programme Officer" means an officer appointed under sub-section (1) of section 15 for`
  line `implementing the Scheme;`
  line
  line `(n) 'project" means any work taken up under a Scheme for the purpose of providing employment`
  line `to the applicants;`
  line
  line `(o) "rural area" means any area in a State except those areas covered by any urban local body or a`
  line `Cantonment Board established or constituted under any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(p) "Scheme" means a Scheme notified by the State Government under sub-section (1) of`
  line section4;
  line
  line `(q) 'State Council" means the State Employment Guarantee Council constituted under subsection`
  line `(1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(r) 'unskilled manual work" means any physical work which any adult person is capable of doing`
  line `without any skill or special training;`
  line
  line `(s) "wage rate" means the wage rate referred to in section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (11852)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Guarantee of rural employment to households.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11852&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided, the State`
  line `Government shall, in such rural area in the State as may be notified by the Central Government, provide`
  line `to every household whose adult members volunteer to do unskilled manual work not less than one`
  line `hundred days of such work in a financial year in accordance with the Scheme made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person who has done the work given to him under the Scheme shall be entitled to receive`
  line `wages at the wage rate for each day of work.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the disbursement of daily wages shall be made on a`
  line `weekly basis or in any case not later than a fortnight after the date on which such work was done.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government or the State Government may, within the limits of its economic capacity`
  line `and development, make provisions for securing work to every adult member of a household under a`
  line `Scheme for any period beyond the period guaranteed under sub-section (1), as may be expedient.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (11853)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Employment Guarantee Schemes for rural areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11853&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of giving effect to the`
  line `provisions of section 3, every State Government shall, within six months from the date of commencement`
  line `of this Act, by notification, make a Scheme, for providing not less than one hundred days of guaranteed`
  line `employment in a financial year to every household in the rural areas covered under the Scheme and`
  line `whose adult members, by application, volunteer to do unskilled manual work subject to the conditions`
  line `laid down by or under this Act and in the Scheme:`
  line
  line `Provided that until any such Scheme is notified by the State Government, the Annual Action Plan or`
  line `Perspective Plan for the Sampoorna Grameen Rozgar Yojana (SGRY) or the National Food for Work`
  line `Programme (NFFWP) whichever is in force in the concerned area immediately before such notification`
  line `shall be deemed to be the action plan for the Scheme for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall publish a summary of the Scheme made by it in at least two local`
  line `newspapers, one of which shall be in a vernacular language circulating in the area or areas to which such`
  line `Scheme shall apply.`
  line
  line `(3) The Scheme made under sub-section (1) shall provide for the minimum features specified in`
  line `Schedule I.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (11854)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Conditions for providing guaranteed employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11854&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, without`
  line `prejudice to the conditions specified in Schedule II, specify in the Scheme the conditions for providing`
  line `guaranteed employment under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The persons employed under any Scheme made under this Act shall be entitled to such facilities`
  line `not less than the minimum facilities specified in Schedule II.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (11855)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Wage rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11855&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Minimum Wages Act, 1948 (11 of`
  line `1948), the Central Government may, by notification, specify the wage rate for the purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that different rates of wages may be specified for different areas:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the wage rate specified from time to time under any such notification shall not`
  line `be at a rate less than sixty rupees per day.`
  line
  line `(2) Until such time as a wage rate is fixed by the Central Government in respect of any area in a State,`
  line `the minimum wage fixed by the State Government under section 3 of the Minimum Wages Act, 1948 (11`
  line `of 1948) for agricultural labourers, shall be considered as the wage rate applicable to that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (11856)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Payment of unemployment allowance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11856&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) If an applicant for employment under the Scheme is`
  line `not provided such employment within fifteen days of receipt of his application seeking employment or`
  line `from the date on which the employment has been sought in the case of an advance application, whichever`
  line `is later, he shall be entitled to a daily unemployment allowance in accordance with this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such terms and conditions of eligibility as may be prescribed by the State Government`
  line `and subject to the provisions of this Act and the Schemes and the economic capacity of the State`
  line `Government, the unemployment allowance payable under sub-section (1) shall be paid to the applicants`
  line `of a household subject to the entitlement of the household at such rate as may be specified by the State`
  line `Government, by notification, in consultation with the State Council:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such rate shall be less than one-fourth of the wage rate for the first thirty days during`
  line `the financial year and not less than one-half of the wage rate for the remaining period of the financial`
  line year.
  line
  line `(3) The liability of the State Government to pay unemployment allowance to a household during any`
  line `financial year shall cease as soon as--`
  line
  line `(a) the applicant is directed by the Gram Panchayat or the Programme Officer to report for work`
  line `either by himself or depute at least one adult member of his household; or`
  line
  line `(b) the period for which employment is sought comes to an end and no member of the household`
  line `of the applicant had turned up for employment; or`
  line
  line `(c) the adult members of the household of the applicant have received in total at least one hundred`
  line `days of work within the financial year; or`
  line
  line `(d) the household of the applicant has earned as much from the wages and unemployment`
  line `allowance taken together which is equal to the wages for one hundred days of work during the`
  line `financial year.`
  line
  line `(4) The unemployment allowance payable to the household of an applicant jointly shall be sanctioned`
  line `and disbursed by the Programme Officer or such local authority (including the Panchayats at the district,`
  line `intermediate or village level) as the State Government may, by notification, authorise in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) Every payment of unemployment allowance under sub-section (1) shall be made or offered not`
  line `later than fifteen days from the date on which it became due for payment.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Government may prescribe the procedure for payment of unemployment allowance`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (11857)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Non-disbursement of unemployment allowance in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11857&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the`
  line `Programme Officer is not in a position to disburse the unemployment allowance in time or at all for any`
  line `reason beyond his control, he shall report the matter to the District Programme Coordinator and announce`
  line `such reasons in a notice to be displayed on his notice board and the notice board of the Gram Panchayat`
  line `and such other conspicuous places as he may deem necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) Every case of non-payment or delayed payment of unemployment allowance shall be reported in`
  line `the annual report submitted by the District Programme Coordinator to the State Government along with`
  line `the reasons for such non-payment or delayed payment.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government shall take all measures to make the payment of unemployment allowance`
  line `reported under sub-section (1) to the concerned household as expeditiously as possible.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (11858)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Disentitlement to receive unemployment allowance in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11858&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `An applicant`
  line who--
  line
  line `(a) does not accept the employment provided to his household under a Scheme; or`
  line
  line `(b) does not report for work within fifteen days of being notified by the Programme Officer or the`
  line `implementing agency to report for the work; or`
  line
  line `(c) continuously remains absent from work, without obtaining a permission from the concerned`
  line `implementing agency for a period of more than one week or remains absent for a total period of more`
  line `than one week in any month,shall not be eligible to claim the unemployment allowance payable under`
  line `this Act for a period of three months but shall be eligible to seek employment under the Scheme at`
  line `any time.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (11859)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Central Employment Guarantee Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11859&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification specify, there shall be constituted a Council to be called the Central`
  line `Employment Guarantee Council to discharge the functions, and perform the duties, assigned to it by or`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The headquarters of the Central Council shall be at Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Council shall consist of the following members to be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) not more than such number of representatives of the Central Ministries including the Planning`
  line `Commission not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India as may be determined`
  line `by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) not more than such number of representatives of the State Governments as may be determined`
  line `by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) not more than fifteen non-official members representing Panchayati Raj Institutions,`
  line `organisations of workers and disadvantaged groups:`
  line
  line `Provided that such non-official members shall include two chairpersons of District Panchayats`
  line `nominated by the Central Government by rotation for a period of one year at a time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that not less than one-third of the non-official members nominated under this`
  line `clause shall be women:`
  line
  line `Provided also that not less than one-third of the non-official members shall be belonging to the`
  line `Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes, the Other Backward Classes and Minorities;`
  line
  line `(e) such number of representatives of the States as the Central Government may, by rules,`
  line `determine in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(f) a Member-Secretary not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India.`
  line
  line `(4) The terms and conditions subject to which the Chairperson and other members of the Central`
  line `Council may be appointed and the time, place and procedure of the meetings (including the quorum at`
  line `such meetings) of the Central Council shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (11860)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Functions and duties of Central Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11860&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Council shall perform and discharge`
  line `the following functions and duties, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) establish a central evaluation and monitoring system;`
  line
  line `(b) advise the Central Government on all matters concerning the implementation of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) review the monitoring and redressal mechanism from time to time and recommend`
  line `improvements required;`
  line
  line `(d) promote the widest possible dissemination of information about the Schemes made under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(e) monitoring the implementation of this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) preparation of annual reports to be laid before Parliament by the Central Government on the`
  line `implementation of this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) any other duty or function as may be assigned to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Council shall have the power to undertake evaluation of the various Schemes made`
  line `under this Act and for that purpose collect or cause to be collected statistics pertaining to the rural`
  line `economy and the implementation of the Schemes.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (11861)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `State Employment Guarantee Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11861&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of regular monitoring and`
  line `reviewing the implementation of this Act at the State level, every State Government shall constitute a`
  line `State Council to be known as the ......(name of the State) State Employment Guarantee Council with a`
  line `Chairperson and such number of official members as may be determined by the State Government and not`
  line `more than fifteen non-official members nominated by the State Government from Panchayati Raj`
  line `institutions, organisations of workers and disadvantaged groups:`
  line
  line `Provided that not less than one-third of the non-official members nominated under this clause shall be`
  line `women:`
  line
  line `Provided further that not less than one third of the non-official members shall be belonging to the`
  line `Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes, the Other Backward Classes and Minorities.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions subject to which the Chairperson and members of the State Council may`
  line `be appointed and the time, place and procedure of the meetings (including the quorum at such meetings)`
  line `of the State Council shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The duties and functions of the State Council shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) advising the State Government on all matters concerning the Scheme and its implementation`
  line `in the State;`
  line
  line `(b) determining the preferred works;`
  line
  line `(c) reviewing the monitoring and redressal mechanisms from time to time and recommending`
  line improvements;
  line
  line `(d) promoting the widest possible dissemination of information about this Act and the Schemes`
  line `under it;`
  line
  line `(e) monitoring the implementation of this Act and the Schemes in the State and coordinating such`
  line `implementation with the Central Council;`
  line
  line `(f) preparing the annual report to be laid before the State Legislature by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(g) any other duty or function as may be assigned to it by the Central Council or the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) The State Council shall have the power to undertake an evaluation of the Schemes operating in the`
  line `State and for that purpose to collect or cause to be collected statistics pertaining to the rural economy and`
  line `the implementation of the Schemes and Programmes in the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (11862)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Principal authorities for planning and implementation of Schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11862&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Panchayats at`
  line `district, intermediate and village levels shall be the principal authorities for planning and implementation`
  line `of the Schemes made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The functions of the Panchayats at the district level shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to finalise and approve blockwise shelf of projects to be taken up under a programme under`
  line `the Scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) to supervise and monitor the projects taken up at the Block level and district level; and`
  line
  line `(c) to carry out such other functions as may be assigned to it by the State Council, from time to`
  line time.
  line
  line `(3) The functions of the Panchayat at intermediate level shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to approve the Block level Plan for forwarding it to the district Panchayat at the district level`
  line `for final approval;`
  line
  line `(b) to supervise and monitor the projects taken up at the Gram Panchayat and Block level; and`
  line
  line `(c) to carry out such other functions as may be assigned to it by the State Council, from time to`
  line time.
  line
  line `(4) The District Programme Coordinator shall assist the Panchayat at the district level in discharging`
  line `its functions under this Act and any Scheme made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (11863)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `District Programme Coordinator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11863&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Executive Officer of the District Panchayat`
  line `or the Collector of the district or any other district level officer of appropriate rank as the State`
  line `Government may decide shall be designated as the District Programme Coordinator for the`
  line `implementation of the Scheme in the district.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Programme Coordinator shall be responsible for the implementation of the Scheme in`
  line `the district in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) The functions of the District Programme Coordinator shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to assist the district Panchayat in discharging its functions under this Act and any scheme`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) to consolidate the plans prepared by the Blocks and project proposals received from other`
  line `implementing agencies for inclusion in the shelf of projects to be approved by the Panchayat at`
  line `district level;`
  line
  line `(c) to accord necessary sanction and administrative clearance, wherever necessary;`
  line
  line `(d) to coordinate with the Programme Officers functioning within his jurisdiction and the`
  line `implementing agencies to ensure that the applicants are provided employment as per their`
  line `entitlements under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) to review, monitor and supervise the performance of the Programme Officers;`
  line
  line `(f) to conduct periodic inspection of the works in progress; and`
  line
  line `(g) to redress the grievances of the applicants.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government shall delegate such administrative and financial powers to the District`
  line `Programme Coordinator as may be required to enable him to carry out his functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The Programme Officer appointed under sub-section (1) of section 15 and all other officers of the`
  line `State Government and local authorities and bodies functioning within the district shall be responsible to`
  line `assist the District Programme Coordinator in carrying out his functions under this Act and the Schemes`
  line `made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(6) The District Programme Coordinator shall prepare in the month of December every year a labour`
  line `budget for the next financial year containing the details of anticipated demand for unskilled manual work`
  line `in the district and the plan for engagement of labourers in the works covered under the Scheme and`
  line `submit it to the district panchayat.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (11864)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Programme Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11864&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) At every Panchayat at intermediate level, the State Government shall`
  line `appoint a person who is not below the rank of Block Development Officer with such qualifications and`
  line `experience as may be determined by the State Government as Programme Officer at the Panchayat at`
  line `intermediate level.`
  line
  line `(2) The Programme Officer shall assist the Panchayat at intermediate level in discharging its`
  line `functions under this Act and any Scheme made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) The Programme Officer shall be responsible for matching the demand for employment with the`
  line `employment opportunities arising from projects in the area under his jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(4) The Programme Officer shall prepare a plan for the Block under his jurisdiction by consolidating`
  line `the project proposals prepared by the Gram Panchayats and the proposals received from intermediate`
  line panchayats.
  line
  line `(5) The functions of the Programme Officer shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) monitoring of projects taken up by the Gram Panchayats and other implementing agencies`
  line `within the Block;`
  line
  line `(b) sanctioning and ensuring payment of unemployment allowance to the eligible households;`
  line
  line `(c) ensuring prompt and fair payment of wages to all labourers employed under a programme of`
  line `the Scheme within the Block;`
  line
  line `(d) ensuring that regular social audits of all works within the jurisdiction of the Gram Panchayat`
  line `are carried out by the Gram Sabha and that prompt action is taken on the objections raised in the`
  line `social audit;`
  line
  line `(e) dealing promptly with all complaints that may arise in connection with the implementation of`
  line `the Scheme within the Block; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other work as may be assigned to him by the District Programme Coordinator or the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(6) The Programme Officers shall function under the direction, control and superintendence of the`
  line `District Programme Coordinator.`
  line
  line `(7) The State Government may, by order, direct that all or any of the functions of a Programme`
  line `Officer shall be discharged by the Gram Panchayat or a local authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (11865)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Responsibilities of the Gram Panchayats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11865&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Gram Panchayat shall be responsible for`
  line `identification of the projects in the Gram Panchayat area to be taken up under a Scheme as per the`
  line `recommendations of the Gram Sabha and the Ward Sabhas and for executing and supervising such works.`
  line
  line `(2) A Gram Panchayat may take up any project under a Scheme within the area of the Gram`
  line `Panchayat as may be sanctioned by the Programme Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Gram Panchayat shall, after considering the recommendations of the Gram Sabha and the`
  line `Ward Sabhas, prepare a development plan and maintain a shelf of possible works to be taken up under the`
  line `Scheme as and when demand for work arises`
  line
  line `(4) The Gram Panchayat shall forward its proposals for the development projects including the order`
  line `of priority between different works to the Programme Officer for scrutiny and preliminary approval prior`
  line `to the commencement of the year in which it is proposed to be executed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Programme Officer shall allot at least fifty per cent. of the works in terms of its cost under a`
  line `Scheme to be implemented through the Gram Panchayats.`
  line
  line `(6) The Programme Officer shall supply each Gram Panchayat with--`
  line
  line `(a) the muster rolls for the works sanctioned to be executed by it; and`
  line
  line `(b) a list of employment opportunities available elsewhere to the residents of the Gram`
  line Panchayat.
  line
  line `(7) The Gram Panchayat shall allocate employment opportunities among the applicants and ask them`
  line `to report for work.`
  line
  line `(8) The works taken up by a Gram Panchayat under a Scheme shall meet the required technical`
  line `standards and measurements.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (11866)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Social audit of work by Gram Sabha.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11866&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Gram Sabha shall monitor the execution of`
  line `works within the Gram Panchayat.`
  line
  line `(2) The Gram Sabha shall conduct regular social audits of all the projects under the Scheme taken up`
  line `within the Gram Panchayat.`
  line
  line `(3) The Gram Panchayat shall make available all relevant documents including the muster rolls, bills,`
  line `vouchers, measurement books, copies of sanction orders and other connected books of account and papers`
  line `to the Gram Sabha for the purpose of conducting the social audit.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (11867)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Responsibilities of State Government in implementing Scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11867&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall`
  line `make available to the District Programme Coordinator and the Programme Officers necessary staff and`
  line `technical support as may be necessary for the effective implementation of the Scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (11868)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Grievance redressal mechanism.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11868&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall, by rules, determine appropriate`
  line `grievance redressal mechanisms at the Block level and the district level for dealing with any complaint by`
  line `any person in respect of implementation of the Scheme and lay down the procedure for disposal of such`
  line complaints.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (11869)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `National Employment Guarantee Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11869&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification,`
  line `establish a fund to be called the National Employment Guarantee Fund for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, after due appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf,`
  line `credit by way of grants or loans such sums of money as the Central Government may consider necessary`
  line `to the National Fund.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount standing to the credit of the National Fund shall be utilised in such manner and`
  line `subject to such conditions and limitations as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (11870)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `State Employment Guarantee Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11870&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification, establish`
  line `a fund to be called the State Employment Guarantee Fund for the purposes of implementation of the`
  line Scheme.
  line
  line `(2) The amount standing to the credit of the State Fund shall be expended in such manner and subject`
  line `to such conditions and limitations as may be prescribed by the State Government for the purposes of`
  line `implementation of this Act and the Schemes made thereunder and for meeting the administrative expenses`
  line `in connection with the implementation of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Fund shall be held and administered on behalf of the State Government in such manner`
  line `and by such authority as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (11871)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Funding pattern.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11871&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the rules as may be made by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf, the Central Government shall meet the cost of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount required for payment of wages for unskilled manual work under the Scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) up to three-fourths of the material cost of the Scheme including payment of wages to skilled`
  line `and semi-skilled workers subject to the provisions of Schedule II;`
  line
  line `(c) such percentage of the total cost of the Scheme as may be determined by the Central`
  line `Government towards the administrative expenses, which may include the salary and allowances of the`
  line `Programme Officers and his supporting staff, the administrative expenses of the Central Council,`
  line `facilities to be provided under Schedule II and such other item as may be decided by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall meet the cost of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the cost of unemployment allowance payable under the Scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) one-fourth of the material cost of the Scheme including payment of wages to skilled and semiskilled`
  line `workers subject to the provisions of Schedule II;`
  line
  line `(c) the administrative expenses of the State Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (11872)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Transparency and accountability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11872&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Programme Coordinator and all`
  line `implementing agencies in the District shall be responsible for the proper utilisation and management of`
  line `the funds placed at their disposal for the purpose of implementing a Scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may prescribe the manner of maintaining proper books and accounts of`
  line `employment of labourers and the expenditure incurred in connection with the implementation of the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the Schemes made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, by rules, determine the arrangements to be made for the proper`
  line `execution of Schemes and programmes under the Schemes and to ensure transparency and accountability`
  line `at all levels in the implementation of the Schemes.`
  line
  line `(4) All payments of wages in cash and unemployment allowances shall be made directly to the person`
  line `concerned and in the presence of independent persons of the community on pre-announced dates.`
  line
  line `(5) If any dispute or complaint arises concerning the implementation of a Scheme by the Gram`
  line `Panchayat, the matter shall be referred to the Programme Officer.`
  line
  line `(6) The Programme Officer shall enter every complaint in a complaint register maintained by him and`
  line `shall dispose of the disputes and complaints within seven days of its receipt and in case it relates to a`
  line `matter to be resolved by any other authority it shall be forwarded to such authority under intimation to the`
  line complainant.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (11873)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Audit of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11873&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor General of India, prescribe appropriate arrangements for audits of the accounts of the Schemes at`
  line `all levels.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Scheme shall be maintained in such form and in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (11874)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Penalty for non-compliance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11874&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes the provisions of this Act shall on`
  line `conviction be liable to a fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (11875)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11875&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, direct that the powers`
  line `exercisable by it (excluding the power to make rules) may, in such circumstances and subject to such`
  line `conditions and limitations, be exercisable also by the State Government or such officer subordinate to the`
  line `Central Government or the State Government as it may specify in such notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification, direct that the powers exercisable by it (excluding the`
  line `power to make rules and Schemes) may, in such circumstances and subject to such conditions and`
  line `limitations, be exercisable also by such officer subordinate to it as it may specify in such notification`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (11876)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11876&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions as it may consider necessary to the State Government for the effective implementation of the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Central Government may, on receipt of`
  line `any complaint regarding the issue or improper utilisation of funds granted under this Act in respect of any`
  line `Scheme if prima facie satisfied that there is a case, cause an investigation into the complaint made by any`
  line `agency designated by it and if necessary, order stoppage of release of funds to the Scheme and institute`
  line `appropriate remedial measures for its proper implementation within a reasonable period of time.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (11877)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11877&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act or the Schemes made thereunder shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being`
  line `in force or in any instrument having effect by virtue of such law:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a State enactment exists or is enacted to provide employment guarantee for`
  line `unskilled manual work to rural households consistent with the provisions of this Act under which the`
  line `entitlement of the households is not less than and the conditions of employment are not inferior to what is`
  line `guaranteed under this Act, the State Government shall have the option of implementing its own`
  line `enactment:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in such cases the financial assistance shall be paid to the concerned State`
  line `Government in such manner as shall be determined by the Central Government, which shall not exceed`
  line `what the State would have been entitled to receive under this Act had a Scheme made under this Act had`
  line `to be implemented.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (11878)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to amend Schedules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11878&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do, it may, by notification, amend Schedule I or Schedule II and thereupon Schedule I or`
  line `Schedule II, as the case may be, shall be deemed to have been amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification made under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of`
  line `Parliament as soon as may be after it is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (11879)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11879&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the District Programme Coordinator, Programme Officer or any other person who is, or who is`
  line `deemed to be, a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) in`
  line `respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules or`
  line `Schemes made thereunder`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (11880)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11880&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, and subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules to carry out the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without the prejudice of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or`
  line `any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the number of representatives of the State Governments under clause (e) of sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) the terms and conditions subject to which the Chairman and other members of the Central`
  line `Council may be appointed, and the time, place and procedure of the meetings (including the quorum`
  line `at such meetings) of the Central Council, under sub-section (4) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which and the conditions and limitations subject to which the National Fund`
  line `shall be utilised under sub-section (3) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(d) the rules relating to funding pattern to meet the cost of certain items under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 22;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which provision is to be`
  line `made by the Central Government by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (11881)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11881&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification,`
  line `and subject to the condition of previous publication, and consistent with this Act and the rules made by`
  line `the Central Government, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions upon which eligibility for unemployment allowance may be`
  line `determined under sub-section (2) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure for payment of unemployment allowance under sub-section (6) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms and conditions subject to which the Chairperson and members of the State Council`
  line `may be appointed, and the time, place and procedure of the meetings (including the quorum at such`
  line `meetings) of their appointment to the State Council, under sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(d) the grievance redressal mechanism at the Block level and the District level and the procedure`
  line `to be followed in such matter under section 19;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which and the conditions and limitations subject to which the State Fund shall`
  line `be utilised under sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(f) the authority who may administer and the manner in which he may hold the State Fund under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of maintaining books of account of employment of labourers and the expenditure`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(h) the arrangements required for proper execution of Schemes under sub-section (3) of section`
  line 23;
  line
  line `(i) the form and manner in which the accounts of the Scheme shall be maintained under subsection`
  line `(2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which provision is to be`
  line `made by the State Government by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (11882)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Laying of rules and Schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11882&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act`
  line `shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session,`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both the Houses agree`
  line `that the rule should not be made, the rule shall have thereafter have effect only in such modified form or`
  line `be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule or Scheme made by the State Government under this Act shall, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, be laid before each House of the State Legislature where there are two Houses, and where`
  line `there is one House of the State Legislature, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (11883)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969&sectionId=11883&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00009_200542_1517807324969
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
